Sentencas: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-delta perovskites with improved redox stability are systematically investigated as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Materials are characterized in terms of their crystal structure, thermal expansion coefficient, oxygen content, transport properties, chemical stability and compatibility with electrolyte, as well as electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Partial substitution of Fe with Ti in Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-delta changes crystal structure with B-site ongoing disordering.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Ti-doping enhances stability of materials in air, but decreases the conductivity.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficients of Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-delta in air are moderate below 600 degrees C, however, an appearance of SrMoO4 at higher temperatures limits their exposure to air.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-delta (x = 0, 0.1) oxides show very high conductivity in 5 vol.% H-2/argon.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The constructed SOFC with Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-delta anode delivers very good power density exceeding 0.64 W cm(2) at 900 degrees C in humidified H-2.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A small total electrode polarization resistance (R-HF+R-LF) is measured, equal to 0.18 Omega cm(2) at 900 degrees C.
Titulo: Ti-doped Sr2Fe1.4-xTixMo0.6O6-δ double perovskites with improved stability as anode materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
